# Python environment: `obd`

This repo’s dependencies (numpy, scipy, sympy, etc.) live in the **conda** environment named **`obd`**.

## When you run terminal commands (agent)

Use the `obd` env so imports work—for example:

- `conda run -n obd python <script.py> [args...]`
- `conda run -n obd python -m pytest ...`

Or run after `conda activate obd` in that shell. Do **not** use bare system `python3` if it may lack packages.

## When you show example commands to the user

Use normal **`python ...`** (no `conda run` prefix). They use the `obd` environment in their own setup; examples should stay short and copy-paste friendly.
